<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Normally when using url view helper</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$this-&gt;url(array('foo' =&gt; 'bar'))
</code></pre>

<p>associative array is being used</p>

<p>However when using this with route</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
  Zend_Controller_Router_Route_Regexabc/([0-9a-z\-]{3,40}).htmlabcindex1abc/%s.html</code></pre>

<p>Too few arguments exception is thrown in Zend_Controller_Router_Route_Regex, because associative array can not be put in vsprintf() therefore i suggest treat urlOptions with array_values() which return zero-based index array which is suitable for vsprintf()</p>

